result.adr_address: 7 Staunton St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Barista by Givrés

reviews.text: Great coffee shop just off of the mid levels escalator, amazing coffee and super friendly staff. Had the Avocado toast and the eggs Benedict, both were perfect. Also serving Gelato!
The best coffee in town!!! Some of my friends spilled the coffee and they don’t hesitate give us a new coffee. Ice cream also good. Must try.We and we will back again soon.
Beautiful coffee with delicate espresso flower. Floating rose costs $80 HKD but it’s definitely a good try. Enjoy a nice time in Soho with this drink :)

Came here mainly for the beautiful flower ice cream.  A lot of work and they looked awesome.  Hk$65 for two favours .. ok with the crafting that needed.   Taste of gelato tended to be a bit too sweet for me.  The Lavender favour is strong and really very Lavender .. 😅
I'd love their strong flavour coffee and brownie (soft with a bit of crunchy on the base).  Great service.
